Agile Software Development (ASD) is a modern software development approach that focuses on building software in small, incremental parts through short development cycles called iterations or sprints. It emphasizes flexibility, continuous customer feedback, teamwork, and quick delivery of working software rather than following a rigid, predefined plan. In Agile, requirements can change at any stage of development, allowing teams to adapt easily and improve the product continuously. This approach helps deliver higher-quality software, reduces risk, and ensures that the final product better meets user needs.